text: Kourtney Jean Keegan (born 7 September 1994) is an American tennis player. Kourtney was born in Chicago, Illinois. She spent some of her youth in Jacksonville, FL before moving back to Chicago, before finally settling down in Roswell, GA throughout high school before going to the University of Florida to play tennis where she won a National Championship. Keegan made her Grand Slam main draw debut at the 2016 US Open in the doubles event, partnering Brooke Austin. She graduated from the University of Florida in 2017 and currently resides in Jacksonville, FL. ==External links== * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:American female tennis players Category:Sportspeople from Chicago Category:People from Roswell, Georgia Category:Florida Gators women's tennis players
